article.headline: Lehigh 71, Navy 61
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. (AP) -- Kyle Neptune and Jose Olivero scored 17 points each as Lehigh won for the first time on the road this season, downing Navy 71-61. The Mountain Hawks (7-10) had lost 11 games on the road this season and 14 regular-season road games dating to last season. They have now started their Patriot League season 2-0 for five straight seasons. Navy (10-7, 0-2) was led by Kaleo Kina with a season-high 23 points, but could not overcome a double-digit halftime deficit. The Mids' high scorer for the season, Greg Sprink, had just 9 points and did not score a basket until the second half. For Lehigh, Marquis Hall added 13 points and seven rebounds. Phil Anderson made 5 of 6 from the floor for 10 points, and Bryan White added 9 points and 7 rebounds. The Mountain Hawks never trailed, jumping to leads of 5-0 and 13-4 to open the game. Lehigh led 34-21 at halftime, led by Olivero's 11 points and trio of 3-pointers, as Navy shot just 30 percent and had 12 turnovers. After Olivero opened the second half with a basket to give Lehigh its biggest lead of the game at 36-21, Navy stormed back with an 18-7 run to get within 43-39 with 12 minutes to play. Trey Stanton hit a three-pointer with 5:51 left to pull Navy to 53-52, but baskets by Olivero and Neptune stretched the lead back to 57-52. Navy closed back to 61-59 after a 3-pointer by Kina with 4:03 to play but Corey Johnson's 3-point try for the lead missed. Lehigh countered with a basket inside by Anderson and a three-pointer by Neptune to go back up 66-59 with 1:48 to play. A free throw by Neptune ended a 6-0 run and stretched the lead to 67-59 with 1:15 left.
